    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Matchlocks in which a cock or serpentine, holding the match, is held pressed into the pan of priming powder by a spring. When the firearm is cocked, the match is held up from the pan; when fired, it snaps rapidly down, igniting the powder.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
